Hong Kong’s PCCW Plans to Launch 4G Service in U.K, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-14T21:15:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/hong-kong-s-pccw-plans-to-launch-4g-service-in-u-k-ft-reports.html
Hong Kong-based telecoms company
 PCCW Ltd. (8)  is planning to build a high-speed broadband network in
the U.K. that could be launched as soon as 2012, the Financial
Times reported, citing Nicholas James, chief executive officer
of the company’s U.K. subsidiary, U.K. Broadband. The network
would be based on fourth-generation wireless technology and
would be dependent on device manufacturers producing the
handsets and equipment to operate on the radio spectrum PCCW
holds, the FT said  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 